    <node id="The cause of headaches, according to the scientists in the story, is an effect that they have identified as being caused by an over-production of the pituitary gland, which leads to a constriction of blood vessels in the telencephalon section of the frontal lobes. This pressure effect on the brain is what produces headaches. The scientists have developed a virus that feeds on pituitrin, a substance responsible for the over-production of the pituitary gland. By artificially breeding this virus, they aim to cure headaches by localizing and stabilizing a colony of the virus in the brain cells, which will relax the cerebral vessels and prevent excessive pressure within the brain cavities. This one simple injection could potentially eradicate headaches forever." />
