    <node id="The story describes the discovery of what the scientists believe to be the &quot;one real cause&quot; of headaches, which is an effect caused by an over-production of the pituitary gland leading to a constriction of blood vessels in the brain. They have developed a virus that feeds on pituitrin, the substance responsible for the over-production of the pituitary gland, and plan to use it to cure headaches by localizing and stabilizing a colony of the virus in the brain cells, which will relax the cerebral vessels and prevent excessive pressure within the brain cavities.&#10;&#10;However, it is important to note that this explanation only addresses one potential cause of headaches, and it is not specified how this single injection could potentially address all types of headaches, which can have various underlying causes including nervous strain, fatigue, physical diseases, and over-indulgence. The scientists themselves acknowledge the existence of different causes for headaches, but they claim to have identified a single effect that they believe is the root cause of all headaches.&#10;&#10;Therefore, it is not accurate to say that the scientists have discovered a single cure for all types of headaches, as they only address one possible cause of headaches with their proposed treatment. It is important to consult with a healthcare professional for proper diagnosis and treatment of headaches, as they can have various underlying causes that require different treatments." />
    <node id="&#10; &quot;When your heart stops, your blood pressure goes to its lowest point,&quot; Mitchell said.&#10; &#10; A dew of perspiration had bloomed on Macklin's forehead. &quot;Is there much risk of that?&quot;&#10; &#10; &quot;Practically none,&quot; Mitchell said. &quot;We have to give you the worst possibilities. All our test animals survived and seem perfectly happy and contented. As I said, the virus is self-stabilizing. Ferris and I are confident that there is no danger.... But we may be wrong.&quot;&#10; &#10; Macklin held his head in both hands. &quot;Why did you two select me ?&quot;&#10; &#10; &quot;You're an important man, doctor,&quot; Ferris said. &quot;Nobody would care if Mitchell or I cured ourselves of headaches—they might not even believe us if we said we did. But the proper authorities will believe a man of your reputation. Besides, neither of us has a record of chronic migraine. You do.&quot;&#10; &#10; &quot;Yes, I do,&quot; Macklin said. &quot;Very well. Go ahead. Give me your injection.&quot;&#10; &#10; Mitchell cleared his throat. &quot;Are you positive, doctor?&quot; he asked uncertainly. &quot;Perhaps you would like a few days to think it over" />
