id.&#10;3. Another complicating factor is that Macklin has a history of vascular spasm and a mild pseudostroke, which puts him at risk for paralysis or even death if the treatment is given without proper medical authorization. Mrs. Macklin argues that no court would give such authority to Ferris and Mitchell.&#10;4. Lastly, Mitchell and Ferris express their inability to undo what they have done to Macklin, which adds to the difficulty of forcing him into being cured. They mention that it might be better to accept the consequences of their actions, including potential legal repercussions, as the Army doesn't like what they have done to him.">
